            "description-detail": "The SpaceX website was created as part of a technical challenge, aimed at demonstrating my ability to develop an application from scratch and continuously enhance it. One of the implemented improvements was the creation of a cron job to reduce excessive consumption of the public SpaceX API, ensuring efficiency and resource optimization.\n\nThe application was developed using React with the Vite framework, enabling a faster development workflow. To streamline the creation and customization of components, I utilized shadcn, which allows for the development of base components that can be tailored to fit the layout. Additionally, I used React Query to consume an external API that I built, ensuring efficient data management within the application.\n\nThe backend was developed with Express, structured modularly to allow for future improvements, such as replacing it with Fastify for better performance and more robust update support. I also implemented end-to-end (E2E) tests to ensure the functionality and quality of the system. These tests were automated using GitHub Actions, configuring scripts to run verifications automatically on every push and pull request.\n\nMoreover, I created a cron job to update the database daily at 9 AM, ensuring that the information is always up-to-date and ready for use.\n\nFinally, I integrated Swagger into the API, providing detailed documentation to facilitate reviews, maintenance, and future improvements to the project.",
